06756nam a22010095i 9789048553853DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20222021ne     fo  d z      eng d  a97890485538537 a10.1515/97890485538532doi  a(DE-B1597)602080  a(OCoLC)1289794478  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL 7aHIS0100002bisacsh04a940.31422300aFriction, Fragmentation, and Diversity :bLocalized Politics of European Memories /ced. by Riikka Taavetti, Ulla Savolainen, Päivi Salmesvuori, Sofia Laine, Kirsti Salmi-Niklander. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2022] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (260 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aHeritage and Memory Studies ;v1500tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tAcknowledgements -- tApproaching Localized Politics of European Memories -- tI Politicized Memories and Pasts -- t1 Mitigating the Difficult Past? -- t2 Remembering the ’68 Movement in Germany -- t3 Queering Victimhood -- t4 Social Memories of Transformative Events in Post-Communist Latvia -- t5 Ishans and Murids before, in and after the Gulag -- tII Friction and Diversity -- t6 Between Closure and Redemption -- t7 Imprisonment Trauma in the Period of the Stalinist Repressions -- t8 Fragmented Construction of Cultural Memories in Turkey -- t9 Survival Strategies Constructed through Material Aspects of Everyday Life in Postwar Soviet Society -- t10 Living Together -- tAbout the Authors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis collection focuses on difficult memories and diverse identities related to conflicts and localized politics of memories. The contemporary and history-oriented case studies discuss politicized memories and pasts, the frictions of justice and reconciliation, and the diversity and fragmentation of difficult memories. The collection brings together methodological discussions from oral history research, cultural memory studies and the study of contemporary protest movements. The politicization of memories is analyzed in various contexts, ranging from everyday interaction and diverse cultural representations to politics of the archive and politics as legal processes. The politicization of memories takes place on multiple analytical levels: those inherent to the sources; the ways in which the collections are utilized, archived, or presented; and in the re-evaluation of existing research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCollective memoryzEurope. 0aMemoryxPolitical aspectszEurope. 4aEurope. 4aEuropean history. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aHistory: theory and methods. 4ac 1500 onwards to present day. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  acultural memory, politics of memory, trauma, justice, reconciliation.1 aArdava-Āboliņa, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBērziņš, Didzis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaphi, Priska, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErkorkmaz, Serpil Açıkalın, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJõesalu, Kirsti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaral, Dilek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoldushko, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKucheva, Anastasia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKõresaar, Ene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaine, Sofia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaine, Sofia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRadzobe, Z